PROHIBITED ACTS (ยง 7-3215)
    No employer or person acting on behalf of an employer shall interfere with,estrain, or otherwise deny the exercise or attempt to exercise of any rightrovided by the Act.
    An employer shall not discharge or discriminate in any manner against anmployee because the employee:
    Opposes any practice by an employer made unlawful by the Act;
    Files or attempts to file a claim or charge for violation of the Act;
    Institutes or attempts to institute an proceeding under the Act;
    Facilitates the institution of a proceeding under the Act;
    Provides information or testimony in connection with an inquiry or proceedingelated to the Act; or
    Uses paid leave in accordance with the Act and this Chapter.
    The Act shall not be construed to prohibit an employer from creating andnforcing a policy that prohibits the improper use of paid leave or thatequires the more frequent certifications from an employee if there is evidenceocumenting a pattern of abuse
      of paid leave. A pattern of abuse may bevidenced by the following:
    Consistent taking of paid leave without the notice required by the Act;
    Consistent taking of leave on days for which vacation or annual leave have beenenied;
    A pattern of taking paid leave on days where the employee is scheduled to work ahift or perform duties perceived as undesirable, including high customer volumeays; or
    A pattern of taking paid leave on Mondays, Fridays, or the day immediatelyreceding or following holidays.
